This paper focuses on the coordination of developers in software projects, which is a key aspect of software engineering. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The paper also uses network analysis to study the coordination structure, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Development and Management). Additionally, the paper discusses the organizational structure of software projects, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
